VACE PIPELINE (Source Prep  Mask Gen  Encode  Merge Back)

1. Source Prep trims the input video to fit target_frames, keeping context frames around the edit region.
2. Mask Generator builds the black/white mask (keep vs generate) and control_frames (source pixels + grey fill for generated regions).
3. VACE Encode converts control_frames + mask into latent embeddings the sampler can condition on.
4. After sampling + decode, Merge Back splices the generated segment into the full original video with optical flow blending at the seams.

Change the mode in Source Prep to switch between End Extend, Middle Extend, Frame Interpolation, etc. The Mask Generator mode is wired automatically.

DECODE & MERGE BACK

WanVideoDecode converts the final latent back to pixel space. Enable VAE tiling here if you're low on VRAM.
VACEMergeBack splices the generated frames into the original full-length video. The vace_pipe from Source Prep carries
trim bounds and context counts  blending is fully automatic. Use 'optical_flow' blend for best seam quality (needs OpenCV),
or fall back to 'alpha' (linear crossfade) or 'none' (hard cut).

VRAM OPTIMIZATION

Current: bf16 models loaded to offload_device (CPU). Models swap to GPU only during inference.
Block Swap is set to 0 (disabled). This is the first thing to change if you run out of VRAM.

 Low VRAM (8-12GB):  Use fp8 models + set Block Swap blocks to 20-30 + enable VAE tiling in Decode
 Medium VRAM (16GB): Use bf16 models + Block Swap blocks 10-15
 High VRAM (24GB+):  Use bf16 models + load_device=main_device (full GPU) + Block Swap 0

The LoRA selectors are pre-wired but currently set to 'none' for the HIGH model. If you swap to non-distilled
base models (Option A or C), connect the matching LightX2V distill LoRA (high_noise for HIGH, low_noise for LOW).

VACE TOOLS  Two-Pass Distilled Video Extension Workflow

This workflow extends or edits a source video using WanVideo VACE with a two-pass distilled sampling strategy:
   Pass 1 (HIGH noise,  > 0.9): Generates coarse structure using the high-noise distilled model
   Pass 2 (LOW noise,  < 0.9): Refines details using the Fun VACE LOW model

Each pass uses a different model optimized for its noise range, cutting total steps from ~30 to just 6.

Pipeline: Load Video  Source Prep  Mask Gen  VACE Encode  Sampler (2-pass)  Decode  Merge Back

 Default config: 6 total steps, shift=6.9, sigma split at 0.9. Adjust STEPS and shift to taste.
   The positive prompt is intentionally empty  VACE uses the source video as the primary conditioning.
